<archetype>

  <archetypetitle>Hedge Wizard</archetypetitle>
  <archetypeid>hedge_wizard</archetypeid>
  <archetypedescription>

    <p>
      Harnessing magic is a difficult and dangerous art.  So dangerous in fact that
      the study and use of magic is tightly controlled by the state.  The Empire's College of Mages
      is a guild, chartered by the emperer to police magic use and users both within and without the empire.
      In addition the college acts as a political body that exists for the protection and advancement of its members.
    </p>

    <p>      
      The College divides all magic users into three groups, namely, members of the college who are referred
      to as Mages, licensed magical practioners who are not members of the college, who are referred to as
      wizards, and those deemed to have transgressed the legal bounds of magic use, know as Warlocks or Witches.
    </p>

    <p>
      The Lex Arcanum is the set of laws that outline the legal uses of magic, which for example prohibits the
      practice of necromancy, mind control and the like.  These laws are policed by an organization within the
      College of Mages called the Collegium Inquisitorum.  The Witch Hunters are a second organization, a branch
      of the Church of Mithras, that polices these laws independently of the College, leading to endless
      friction between the Church and the College.
    </p>
    
    <p>
      Hedge Wizards are wandering mages, they make their money in side shows, by grifting, in displays
      of minor magical feats for the entertainment of young children, by providing mystic readings for
      young women and the love-lorn, or through mercenary work.
    </p>

    <figure>
      <img src="./resources/hedge_wizard/the_crooked_staff_by_dw_miller_by_conceptsbymiller-day36nr.png"
	   scale="0.28"/>
    </figure>        

    <p>
      There are many reasons Wizards might not be members of the College, they may be independently minded,
      they may wish to pursue their craft without drawing attention to themselves, or they may have been excluded
      from the college due to internal political infighting.  Hedge wizards are mostly left
      to their own business.  They are however required to be licensed as users of magick and produce said
      license upon request.  They are required to practice their craft in accordance with the
      Lex Arcanaum.  They are referred to officially as non-collegiate magical practitioners.
      Possesion of the license grants immunity from persecution by the Witch Hunters provided there
      has been no infringement of the Lex Arcanum.
    </p>

  </archetypedescription>
